==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ebullioscope
<hw>E*bul"li*o*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ebullire</ets> to boil up + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Phys.
Chem.)</fld> <def>An instrument for observing the boiling point of
liquids, especially for determining the alcoholic strength of a mixture
by the temperature at which it boils.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ebullition</ent>⟦br⟧
